20. cedere loco: the regular idiom for deserting one's post. Roman military theory disapproved even of strategio with- drawals; failure to maintain a prescribed position rendered soldjers liable to severe penalty, as the following passage in the Isise os Auqustus, written by Suetonius, a contemporary of Taci- tus, well attests ε ‘ If any cohorts gave way in battle (si cessissent loco), Augustus decimated them and fed the rest on barley (in- stead of the usual rations of wheat) ; when centurions left their posts‚ he punished them with death just as he did the rank and file' (ehap. 24, Rolfe's translation).
